  "prompt": "How much does CSIS pay new grad software engineers?",
  "response": "As of the most recent available information, the Canadian Security Intelligence Service (CSIS) typically offers competitive salaries for new graduate software engineers, which are aligned with federal government pay scales. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **Entry-Level Positions**: New graduate software engineers at CSIS would likely start at the CS (Computer Systems) group level. Specifically, they might be hired at the CS-01 or CS-02 level.\n\n   - **CS-01**: This is the entry-level position. The salary range for a CS-01 is approximately $62,000 to $82,000 per year.\n   - **CS-02**: If the candidate has more experience or advanced qualifications, they might start at the CS-02 level, which typically ranges from $75,000 to $93,000 per year.\n\n2. **Benefits**: In addition to the base salary, CSIS employees receive benefits such as:\n   - Health and dental insurance\n   - Pension plan\n   - Paid vacation and sick leave\n   - Opportunities for professional development and training\n\n3. **Location**: Salaries may vary slightly based on the location of the position. For example, positions in cities with a higher cost of living, such as Ottawa, might offer slightly higher compensation.\n\n4. **Security Clearance**: Given the nature of CSIS\u2019s work, all employees must obtain and maintain a high-level security clearance, which is a prerequisite for employment.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it\u2019s recommended to check the official CSIS or Government of Canada job postings or contact their Human Resources department directly.",
